<subSubSection id="FEEA6553FF9CFFF6FF53FA12C526F810" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="B64F36D8FF9CFFF6FF53FA12C5D2F880" blockId="10.[151,1436,1417,2018]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="8484EACAFF9CFFF6FF53FA12C54EFA2B" bold="true" box="[199,512,1417,1442]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">Description. Male―Head:</emphasis>
pale brown to yellowish, with some darker areas covered by short setae, except for two areas just above each antennal scape frons and gena (
<figureCitation id="2ECB2A5DFF9CFFF6FC81FA36C417FA4C" box="[789,857,1453,1477]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1253,1276]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1232]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Pepoyara jagoy de Mello &amp; Capellari gen. n.: A— male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B— male lateral head; C— front view of male head; D— posterior legs; E— dorsal spur of hind tibiae of male; F— Female head and pronotum, dorsal view; G— dorsal spur of hind tibiae of male; H— I apical-internal spur of hind tibiae of male; I— ovipositor lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212433/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number id="003824FFFF9CFFF6FCDEFA36C417FA4C" box="[842,857,1453,1477]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C); presence of a group of large, black bristles on each side of vertex and two rows of equally large bristles extending from ocellar triangle to the margin of frons. Clypeus and labrum dark yellow, antennal scape very large. Maxillary palpi as in 
<figureCitation id="2ECB2A5DFF9CFFF6FBA5FA6EC33AF984" box="[1073,1140,1525,1549]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1253,1276]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1232]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Pepoyara jagoy de Mello &amp; Capellari gen. n.: A— male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B— male lateral head; C— front view of male head; D— posterior legs; E— dorsal spur of hind tibiae of male; F— Female head and pronotum, dorsal view; G— dorsal spur of hind tibiae of male; H— I apical-internal spur of hind tibiae of male; I— ovipositor lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212433/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number id="003824FFFF9CFFF6FBF1FA6EC33AF984" box="[1125,1140,1525,1549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
B. 
<emphasis id="8484EACAFF9CFFF6FB00FA6EC3B8F984" bold="true" box="[1172,1270,1525,1549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">Thorax:</emphasis>
disc of pronotum medium brown on a yellowish background, covered by many black, little to median-sized bristles and some larger scattered ones on the disc, lateral lobes dark brown. Fore wings as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2ECB2A5DFF9CFFF6FBD8F9A6C3E2F9DC" box="[1100,1196,1597,1621]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1253,1276]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1232]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Pepoyara jagoy de Mello &amp; Capellari gen. n.: A— male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B— male lateral head; C— front view of male head; D— posterior legs; E— dorsal spur of hind tibiae of male; F— Female head and pronotum, dorsal view; G— dorsal spur of hind tibiae of male; H— I apical-internal spur of hind tibiae of male; I— ovipositor lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/212433/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">
Figure 
<number id="003824FFFF9CFFF6FB09F9A6C3E2F9DC" box="[1181,1196,1597,1621]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
A. 
<emphasis id="8484EACAFF9CFFF6FB5BF9A6C25EF9DC" bold="true" box="[1231,1296,1597,1621]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">Legs:</emphasis>
femora yellowish, I and II with some light brown spots dorsally, III obliquely striped light brown and yellowish on external face; tibiae III yellowish to light brown; tarsi yellowish; hind basitarsus with an external apical spur just about as long as the last two joints. 
<emphasis id="8484EACAFF9CFFF6FE54F932C570F94B" bold="true" box="[448,574,1705,1730]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">Abdomen:</emphasis>
terga dark brown, with some dark yellow spots on tergites 
<number id="003824FFFF9CFFF6FB45F932C3B0F948" box="[1233,1278,1705,1729]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6–9</number>
; sternites pale brown to yellow; supra-anal and subgenital plates brown; cerci as long as abdomen, yellowish. 
<emphasis id="8484EACAFF9CFFF6FB40F956C2D5F96C" bold="true" box="[1236,1435,1741,1766]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">Phallic complex:</emphasis>
as described for the genus, Fig. 08A, B and C.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B64F36D8FF9CFFF6FF53F88EC526F810" blockId="10.[151,1436,1417,2018]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="8484EACAFF9CFFF6FF53F88EC674F8A4" bold="true" box="[199,314,1813,1837]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">Female—</emphasis>
Very similar to males, except as follows: fore wings shorter, extending up to third abdominal tergite. Abdomen medium brown with yellow spots on tergites 
<number id="003824FFFF9CFFF6FC88F8A2C407F8D8" box="[796,841,1849,1873]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" value="5.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="2.0">2–9</number>
; posterior margins of tergites, specially on 
<number id="003824FFFF9CFFF6FAD4F8A2C200F8D8" box="[1344,1358,1849,1873]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" value="6.0">6</number>
th– 
<number id="003824FFFF9CFFF6FAE0F8A2C2CEF8D8" box="[1396,1408,1849,1873]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" value="8.0">8</number>
th, with some large bristles. Ovipositor 
<emphasis id="8484EACAFF9CFFF6FDA5F8C5C51CF8FC" box="[561,594,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="29">ca.</emphasis>
<number id="003824FFFF9CFFF6FDCEF8C6C5C5F8FC" box="[602,651,1885,1909]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" value="1.56">1.56</number>
times longer than pronotum length, dark yellow at base and brown at apex; apical valves with teeth on dorsum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
